  "prompt": "Can I use an unverified Paypal account to receive payments?",
  "response": "An unverified PayPal account has certain limitations, including lower transaction limits and some restrictions on receiving payments. While you can still receive payments with an unverified account, the sender may face limitations on the amount they can send, and you might encounter delays or restrictions in accessing the funds.\n\nTo increase your transaction limits and fully utilize PayPal's services, it's recommended to verify your account by linking and confirming a bank account, credit card, or providing other required identification. This process enhances the security of your account and enables smoother transactions.",
